This the test framework based on leveldb db_bench.
The framework will support storage engines as follows:
LevelDB		(Done)		version 1.5  test
Rocksdb		(Done) 		version 2.5  test
Redis		(Done)  	version 3.0.6 test
Wiredtiger	(Done) 		version 2.7.0 test
Narkdb		(Done)  	version ??    test
Bdb		(Done)			     untest
Mdb		(Done)			     untest
Tree_db		(Done)			     untest
Sqlite3		(Done)			     untest

These test codes are in doc/bench/

Now, the test framework supports fillrandom and readrandom benchmarks for the each dbs, and next step, we will implement other benchmarks.

## How to build db_bench_* (e.g. db_bench_nark)

1. modify Makefile to add "NARK_INCLUDE_PATH", and NARK_INCLUDE_PATH includes nark-db/src
									      nark-bone/src
									      nark-serialization/src
									      nark-hashmap/src

2. create symlink: libnark-g++-4.9-r.so libnark-NarkDB-g++-4.9-r.so in /usr/lib64

3. run "make db_bench_nark"

## How to run db_bench_nark
for example: ./db_bench_nark --benchmarks=fillrandom,readrandom --value_size=64 --num=10000 --db=data



